</code></pre>

Fully meshed flows between four ports.  Each port sends flows to all the ports (except itself).  This example is for four ports, it can be easily extended to an arbitrary number of ports. snappijson <pre><code>import itertools

for i in range(1, 4):
  config.ports.port(name='p%d' % i, \
    location='localhost:%d' % (5554 + i))

for tx, rx in \
  itertools.permutations([p.name for \ 
  p in config.ports], 2):
  f = config.flows.flow(name='flow %s-&gt;%s' \ 
    % (tx, rx))[-1]
  f.tx_rx.port.tx_name = tx
  f.tx_rx.port.rx_name = rx
</code></pre> <pre><code>{
